## Agent final message

> Query written to `query80.preql` and validated. The query:
> 
> 1. Imports `raw.all_sales` (the multi-channel consolidated fact)
> 2. Applies date filter (2000-08-23 through 2000-09-22), item price > 50, promotion TV flag = 'N', and outlet existence check
> 3. Computes channel labels ('store channel', 'catalog channel', 'web channel') and outlet identifiers (prefixed business codes)
> 4. Uses `def rollup_metrics(metric) -> sum(metric) by rollup ch_label, outlet_id_label` to produce per-outlet rows, per-channel subtotals, and a grand total in one pass
> 5. Reports sales (ext_sales_price), returns (coalesced return_amount), and profit (net_profit minus coalesced return_net_loss)
> 6. Orders by channel then outlet with nulls first, limited to 100 rows
> 
> `trilogy run query80.preql` completes successfully — 428 total rows in the result (100 displayed). Output includes the grand total, all three channel subtotals, and per-outlet detail rows.

